  "title": "Civil & Structural (C&S) Coordinator",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coordinate and supervise civil and structural works at the site to ensure compliance with design, quality, and safety standards.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with consultants, architects, and subcontractors to resolve technical and site issues.</li>\n  <li>Review structural and architectural drawings, method statements, and work schedules.</li>\n  <li>Monitor progress and provide regular updates to the Project Manager.</li>\n  <li>Conduct site inspections and ensure workmanship meets regulatory and project requirements.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with building codes, local authorities' requirements, and workplace safety standards.</li>\n  <li>Assist in managing permits, inspections, and documentation for civil/structural works.</li>\n  <li>Provide technical support during installation, testing, and commissioning phases.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Civil Engineering, Structural Engineering, or related field.</li>\n  <li>Minimum <strong>3–5 years</strong> of relevant experience in C&amp;S coordination in construction projects.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of local building codes and regulations.</li>\n  <li>Ability to interpret engineering and structural drawings.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with site safety protocols and coordination of site activities.</li>\n  <li>Good communication, coordination, and problem-solving skills.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Office and AutoCAD (or other CAD software).</li>\n</ul>",
